The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 Ujjain, Dec. 31 (PTI): An eight-year-old boy died after falling into a 200-foot-deep borewell despite a rescue by the district administration. Kalu Singh was trapped at a depth of 40 feet after he slipped and fell into the well yesterday. 

 He was pulled out early today but died before he could be treated.

 New Delhi (PTI): Air services to and from Delhi were disrupted as dense fog engulfed the runway at the airport reducing visibility to near zero. Several trains were also delayed, while drivers on the capitals roads kept their fog lights on. 

 Srinagar (PTI): A man allegedly shot at his 16-year-old son after arguing over a pigeon. Nazir Ahmed Akhoon, who sells pigeons, shot son Abid Ali in the forehead in a fit of rage. Abid was rushed to hospital where his condition was said to be stable. Akhoon has been arrested.

 Chennai (PTI): Dancer and choreographer Chandralekha died on Saturday. She was 78 and was suffering from cancer. A Bharatnatyam soloist in the 1950s, she caught the public imagination through her innovation and experiments with various dance forms.

 Jammu (PTI): Nearly 69 lakh pilgrims have visited the Vaishnodevi shrine in 2006 compared with 62 lakh in 2005. Till now, 68.7 lakh pilgrims have completed the yatra and by night it will reach 69 lakh, a shrine board official said. 

 Hyderabad (PTI): Police have killed three Maoists in an exchange of fire in Khammam district. The rebels died in the retaliatory fire after they attacked a special team combing the Paritalalanka forests, the police said. But some of the Maoists escaped. Four weapons have been found at the spot.




